{
  "stem": "18102.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And they were followed by trucks, hundreds and hundreds of trucks.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And on these trucks, inside them-- some of the trucks were covered wagons.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Some of them were open-- German soldiers all in helmets and with guns.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And of course, you've seen this scene, I'm sure, in movies as the, as the, as the, the enemy soldiers came into a foreign city like Bialystok was.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "That was the-- the rumbling of the tanks and the, the vehicles that followed is something you don't forget because, first of all, it lasted a long time.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "I don't know if it didn't last many hours into the night.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "Eventually I stopped watching.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "But it was a frightening, frightening, feeling.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "I knew war wasn't sword fighting on the big streets.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, at this point, my mother-- after a few days, there were proclamations, and you couldn't-- 6 o'clock curfew.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You couldn't congregate in the streets.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Everybody had to register.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So there was all kinds of proclamations.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] There were also rumors that began to infiltrate the Jewish community about special atrocities, not ghetto or anything like that, not anything near extermination that eventually came about.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "These were the kind of atrocities where a particular individual, usually a Jew, was accosted by soldiers, beaten up, or ridiculed in one fashion or another.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there were many stories about that kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the incident I saw wasn't someone getting beat up.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I saw something far worse.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We lived, as I said, on the outskirts of Bialystok, and it overlooked a cemetery.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The-- it was a Jewish cemetery, actually.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The cemetery, however, was a convenient shortcut into town that was used during the day quite often by people that lived in the surrounding area, not necessarily Jews.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
